# Patch P8 — peft tuners/lora/bnb.py ~L267 and ~L549
# LoRA output device normalization (two occurrences)
#
# Problem: LoRA adds a low-rank update: output = base_result + lora_A * lora_B * x
# When base_result is on cuda:1 (GPU1) but the LoRA adapters run on cuda:0 (GPU0),
# the addition crashes with device mismatch.
# This happens because LoRA adapters are always on the main device (cuda:0)
# but base model weights may be distributed.
#
# Fix: Move LoRA output to result.device before addition.
# Must be applied at BOTH occurrences in peft/tuners/lora/bnb.py.

# BEFORE (original, ~L267 and ~L549):
        result = result + output

# AFTER (PATCH sirfyyn P8):
        result = result + output.to(result.device)  # PATCH sirfyyn P8
